<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 15:50:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Wednesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *American Home Products Corp., down 2 5/32 at 41    	
</P>
<P>
	Opening statements have begun in the first class-action suit to  
come to trial against American Home Products, the maker of half of 
the fen-phen diet drug combination. The company could be forced to 
pay more than $1 billion over the next decade if it loses the civil 
case. 

</P>
<P>
 *Reinsurance Group, down 4 at 32 5/16  
</P>
<P>
 *Conning Corp., down 4 to 12 1/8 on the Nasdaq 
</P>
<P>
	The majority owner of Reinsurance Group and Conning, General  
American Life Insurance Co., has turned to regulators to help it 
pay back $6.8 billion in customers' deposits. Reinsurance Group 
provides reinsurance and Conning is the asset manager for General 
American. 

</P>
<P>
 *Oakwood Homes Corp., down 1 9/16 at 7 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Oakwood, a manufactured home company, has stopped production at  
three plants, reduced production at others, and cut about 1,000 
jobs to date. Citing poor financial performance, Oakwood said it 
has ended its efforts to sell or merge the company. 

</P>
<P>
 *SLI Inc., up 3 1/8 at 25 1/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The company, a maker of miniature lighting products for the  
electronics, automotive and appliance industries, earned 39 cents 
per share in the second quarter. Analysts surveyed by First Call 
Corp. had anticipated profits of 38 cents per share. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Cisco Systems Inc., up 4 3/16 at 62 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Cisco earned $727 million, or 21 cents per share, in its fourth  
quarter ended July 31, slightly beating analysts' expectations. 
Quarterly revenues soared 48 percent due to heavy demand for 
Internet and other network equipment. 

</P>
