<HEADLINE> U.S. Women's Cup Soccer Sked Set </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Following its victory in the Women's World Cup,  
the United States will play three nations in the U.S. Women's Cup 
'99 tournament in October. 
</P>
<P>
	The Americans, who won their second world championship in the  
1990s, will play opponents to be determined during doubleheaders on 
Oct. 3 at Columbus, Ohio, Oct. 7 at Kansas City, Mo., and Oct. 10 
at Louisville, Ky. 
</P>
<P>
	Each of the four nations will play three games, with the winner  
of the round-robin tournament decided on points. 
</P>
<P>
	The United States is 15-0 in the U.S. Women's Cup, which began  
in 1999, outscoring opponents 64-6. 
</P>
<P>
	The tournament is sponsored by Nike.  



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
