<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> European Champions Cup Roundup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	U.S. midfielder Claudio Reyna scored with 14 minutes remaining  
Wednesday night as Glasgow Rangers beat visiting Parma 2-0 in the 
first leg of their European Champions Cup qualifier. 
</P>
<P>
	With Parma playing a man short following the ejection of star  
defender Fabio Cannavaro in the 26th minute, Glasgow went ahead in 
the 32nd minute after goalkeeper Gianluigi Buffon blocked Reyna's 
shot and Tony Vidmar scored off a pass from Neil McCann. 
</P>
<P>
	The second leg of the home-and-home, total-goals series will be  
played at Parma on Aug. 25. Parma ousted Rangers from the UEFA Cup 
last season on the way to winning the title. 
</P>
<P>
	Many of Europe's bigger teams had byes in the first two rounds  
of qualifying. The 16 teams advancing from third and final round of 
qualifying will join Europe's top 16 teams from last season in the 
first round and be drawn into eight four-team groups. 
</P>
<P>
	Fiorentina, returning to the competition after 30 years, beat  
Poland's Widzew Lodz 3-1 on goals by Daniele Adani, Sandro Cois and 
Manuel Rui Costa. Adani put the ball in his own net for Lodz's 
goal. 
</P>
<P>
	Chelsea won 3-0 at Latvia's Skonto Riga, which played  
short-handed after defender Andrejs Terekins was ejected in the 
35th minute. Celestine Babayaro scored in the 75th minute, and 
Gustavo Poyet and Chris Sutton added goals. 
</P>
<P>
	Borussia Dortmund, which won the tournament three years ago, won  
1-0 at FK Teplice of the Czech Republic on Christian Nerlinger's 
goal in the 65th minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Dynamo Kiev, which reached the semifinal last season but still  
had to qualify, won 2-1 at Denmark's Aalborg on goals by Sergei 
Rebrov and Maxim Shatskikh. 
</P>
<P>
	Alexander Shirko scored one goal and assisted another one as  
Spartak Moscow beat Partizan Belgrade 2-0. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
