<HEADLINE> AP Correct Talk Show Slaying Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PONTIAC, Mich. (AP) -- In an Aug. 10 story about the second trial  
of a man who killed an acquaintance after they appeared on a taping 
of ``The Jenny Jones Show,'' The Associated Press erroneously 
reported that a civil jury in May found both Jenny Jones and her 
show liable in the acquaintance's death. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Jones was not a defendant. The jury found ``The Jenny Jones  
Show'' negligent in the slaying of a guest killed after he revealed 
a gay crush on another guest, and ordered it to pay more than $25 
million in damages. 
  	   	
</P>
