<HEADLINE> Rem Murray Re-Signs With Oilers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EDMONTON, Alberta (AP) -- Rem Murray re-signed with the Edmonton  
Oilers on Wednesday, avoiding an arbitration hearing that was 
scheduled in Toronto. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms were not announced.  
</P>
<P>
	Murray, 27, scored 21 goals and had 18 assists last season, his  
third in the NHL. In 221 career games, the left wing has 41 goals 
and 47 assists. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's always preferable to arrive at a mutually agreeable  
contract rather than go through arbitration,'' said Doug 
Risebrough, the Oilers' vice-president of hockey operations. ``This 
is a fair contract, and now we hope Rem will continue to improve.'' 
  	   	
</P>
