<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boldon Pulls Out of Zurich Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) -- World 200-meter champion Ato Boldon  
pulled out of Wednesday night's Golden League track meet because of 
a lingering hamstring injury and ruled himself out of the World 
Championships later this month. 
</P>
<P>
	Boldon, who has not run an individual race since straining his  
hamstring during warmups at the Golden League meet in Paris on July 
21, said his injury appeared worse than first thought and was not 
recovering as expected. 
</P>
<P>
	Boldon made a tentative return to competition last Saturday,  
running in the 400-meter relay at Cyrstal Palace in London. He was 
scheduled to run in the 100 and 200 at the Weltklasse Golden League 
meet in Zurich but pulled out hours before the event. 
</P>
<P>
	``I will not be going to Seville,'' where the World  
Championships begin Aug. 21, Boldon said. ``I made the decision 
and, though I'm not happy about it, it wouldn't be smart to go.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Boldon is the training partner of American sprinter Maurice  
Greene, who set a world record of 9.79 seconds in the 100 meters in 
Athens on June 16. Boldon has twice run 9.86 in the 100 this season 
and has posted the fastest time (19.86) in the 200 this year. 
</P>
<P>
	``I do not believe anyone has a chance to beat Maurice in  
Seville,'' Boldon said. ``What bothers me most is that I felt 
Maurice and I could provide something special there.'' 
</P>
<P>
	But ``I don't want to be stupid. I don't want to get there and  
say, 'well, maybe the 200.''' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
