<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> McGwire Sits Out With Back Pain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Mark McGwire, the major league leader with  
44 homers, missed Wednesday night's game against the Phillies due 
to tightness in his lower back. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire left the game Tuesday night in the second inning after  
walking in his only plate appearance. He said he felt tightness in 
his lower back and came out as a precaution. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire, who put on two sensational batting practice shows  
before the first two games of the series, did not take BP 
Wednesday. He was not in uniform at game time and was doubtful to 
be available to pinch hit. 
</P>
<P>
	The Cardinals are off Thursday, and trainer Barry Weinberg said  
McGwire likely will return to the lineup Friday against the Chicago 
Cubs and Sammy Sosa at Busch Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire has battled back problems since 1989 and missed three  
games last month due to back spasms. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's something I'll have to deal with the rest of my life,''  
McGwire said. 
</P>
<P>
	He hasn't homered in 13 at-bats since hitting his 500th and  
501st last Thursday against San Diego. He was 1-for-10 with no 
extra-base hits in a four-game series at Pittsburgh over the 
weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire's longest homerless drought this season was 41 at-bats,  
between his fifth and sixth homers of the season. He has gone 15 
at-bats without a homer only five times this season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
