<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jets' Testaverde's Thumb OK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) -- Vinny Testaverde's jammed thumb isn't  
serious enough to keep him out of Saturday's preseason game. 
</P>
<P>
	When the New York Jets veteran quarterback injured his thumb  
during Tuesday afternoon's workout, it created a ripple of concern. 
But he practiced Wednesday with little pain. 
</P>
<P>
	Testaverde, who iced his hand after getting hurt Tuesday, is  
expected to start Saturday's preseason opener at Green Bay, playing 
into the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm trying to get the swelling out,'' Testaverde said before  
the afternoon session at the club's training camp facility at 
Hofstra University. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've done it before,'' Testaverde said of the injury,  
sustained when his throwing hand collided with a defensive 
lineman's hand during a passing drill. 
</P>
<P>
	He also suffered a slight tear of skin near his thumbnail, but  
Jets coach Bill Parcells didn't overly concerned. 
</P>
<P>
	``That wasn't anything,'' coach Bill Parcells said of  
Testaverde' problem. ``It's nothing.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Yet, any pain is a concern to the Jets, whose quarterback  
situation beyond Testaverde is uncertain. Scott Zolak, signed away 
from the Patriots during the offseason, hasn't been sharp in the 
early days of training camp. Converted special-teams ace Ray Lucas, 
battling with Zolak for the backup role, is a longshot to earn the 
position. 
</P>
<P>
	But Lucas will get the majority of snaps after Testaverde leaves  
against the Packers. 
</P>
<P>
	Punter Tom Tupa, who can also play quarterback, has seen plenty  
of action in practices. But Parcells has stressed that Tupa, also a 
former Patriot, was brought in to punt. 
</P>
<P>
	Testaverde stressed that he'll be ready to go against the  
Packers. 
</P>
<P>
	``You always get little injuries during the season,'' he said.  
``There are the ones that you are concerned with and the ones not 
to be concerned with. I would put this one as not to be concerned 
with -- from my perspective.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Not playing in Saturday's preseason game will be tight ends  
Blake Spence, nursing a slightly separated shoulder, and Lawrence 
Hart, whose left swollen eye after being poked in practice. 
Additionally, cornerbacks Otis Smith, sidelined with a broken left 
collarbone, and Del Lee, limping with a hamstring, will not play. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
