<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Wednesday, Aug. 11, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	Dow Surges 132.65 to 10,787.80  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks made their broadest, sharpest gains of  
August today as the Federal Reserve offered calming words on the 
growth of the U.S. economy and Cisco Systems provided proof of 
strong corporate earnings. At the close of trading, the Dow Jones 
industrial average was up 132.65 points at 10,787.80. Broader stock 
indicators were also higher. The Nasdaq composite index had its 
biggest point gain, 74.87, since June 16. It was at 2,564.98. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at Wednesday's close:  
Dow Industrials:        10,787.80 + 132.65
NYSE Issues:         Advances 1869  Declines 1154  Unchgd  526
NYSE Volume:         763,776,870
