	Southwest Airlines CEO Has Cancer  
</P>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- Herb Kelleher, the flamboyant chief executive of  
Southwest Airlines, said today that he has prostate cancer, which 
his doctor said was caught in the early stages. Kelleher, 68, who 
pioneered no-frills, low-cost air service and built Southwest into 
one of the country's top airlines, began radiation treatment today. 
Analysts were reassured by an upbeat prognosis from doctors, though 
they remain concerned about who will succeed the colorful, 
68-year-old executive. Southwest stock fell 1/8 at 16 3/8. 

