<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Happyanunoit Wins Palomar Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Happyanunoit, a 13-1 longshot, took the  
lead midway through the stretch and held off 3-5 favorite Tuzla by 
a length to win today's $134,750 Palomar Handicap at Del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Brice Blanc and carrying 113 pounds, Happyanunoit  
covered 1 1-16 miles on turf in a stakes-record 1:41 1-5 and paid 
$28.80, $5.60 and $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
	The race went from one mile on turf to 1 1-16 miles in 1988.  
</P>
<P>
	The fifth victory in nine lifetime starts for the New  
Zealand-bred Happyanunoit was worth $68,750. 
</P>
<P>
	Tuzla, ridden by Corey Nakatani and carrying 123 pounds, crossed  
the finish line a half-length in front of Isle De France and 
returned $2.40 and $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
	Tuzla won the race last year in 1:42 1-5.  
</P>
<P>
	Isle De France, ridden by Chris McCarron and carrying 118  
pounds, was 1 1/2 lengths ahead of Sapphire Ring at the wire and paid 
$2.10 to show in the 46th running of the race for fillies and 
mares. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
