<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> VA Chief Under Nixon Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Donald Johnson, a World War II army veteran  
who headed the Veterans Administration during the last years of the 
Vietnam War, has died of complications of Cancer. He was 75. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson, who headed the VA from 1969 to 1974, died Tuesday at  
Mary Washington Hospital in Fredericksburg, Va., The Washington 
Post reported. 
</P>
<P>
	He resigned in 1974 under criticism for the Nixon  
administration's proposal to cut benefits for disabled Vietnam 
veterans. He later served as a top official in the Commerce 
Department, as chief of staff to Sen. Roger W. Jepson, R-Iowa, and 
then as executive director of the National Credit Union 
Administration. He retired in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
	He is survived by his wife, Mary Jean Johnson, six sons, four  
daughters, 16 grandchildren and a great-grandson. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
