<HEADLINE> Yankees Have Another Bench Clearing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Five days after a brawl at Seattle, the  
New York Yankees found themselves in another bench-clearing 
incident Wednesday night against the Oakland Athletics -- but this 
time no punches were thrown. 
</P>
<P>
	Both dugouts emptied in the first inning after Oakland's Tony  
Phillips, trying to score from second on a single by Randy Velarde, 
barreled into New York catcher Jorge Posada. 
</P>
<P>
	Posada held on to tag Phillips out, and then punched the air  
with his fist. It was unclear whether Posada was celebrating the 
out or gesturing toward Phillips, who immediately began arguing 
with the catcher. 
</P>
<P>
	Although both benches emptied, most players left the field  
laughing. 
</P>
<P>
	New York pitcher Jason Grimsley began serving a three-game  
suspension Wednesday for his part in inciting the brawl last week 
against the Mariners. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
