<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Elvis Tourist Complex Gets Hotel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) -- Pilgrims for the 22nd anniversary of Elvis  
Presley's death on Aug. 16, 1977, have a new place to visit -- and 
yes, it's down at the end of Lonely Street. 
</P>
<P>
	The Heartbreak Hotel is the newest addition to the sprawling  
tourist complex at Presley's former Memphis residence, Graceland. 
And the 128-room hotel is done up in a way the King would have 
loved. 
</P>
<P>
	``We took some cues from Elvis' personal style and the eras he  
represents, the '50s, '60s, '70s, and mixed in a kind of campy 
elegance and modernized retro. We just wanted it to be cool,'' said 
Todd Morgan, director of creative services for Elvis Presley 
Enterprises Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	Graceland and its 50-acre complex of souvenir shops, museums and  
business offices draw more than 700,000 tourists a year. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
