<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	

</P>
<P>
	Sean Penn, born on Aug. 17, 1960, is one of the stars of Woody  
Allen's new film, ``Sweet and Lowdown.'' The film, which also stars 
Uma Thurman, will be shown out of competition at this year's Venice 
Film Festival on Sept. 5. 

</P>
<P>
	Filming is scheduled to get under way this month in Longview,  
Wash., on ``Navy Diver,'' starring Robert DeNiro, who was born on 
Aug. 17, 1943. The film also stars Cuba Gooding Jr. 

</P>
<P>
	Angela Bassett was named outstanding actress at this year's  
NAACP Image Awards. Bassett, who was born on Aug. 16, 1958, won for 
her performance in ``How Stella Got Her Groove Back.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Country singer Kenny Rogers says he got his street smarts  
growing up in a housing project in Houston. ``As a child, this is 
where the foundation for me and my family was laid. It was a 
wonderful experience to be in a place like this,'' said Rogers as 
he toured the newly renovated Allen Parkway Village. ``It's a very 
real part of my history.'' Rogers, who was born on Aug. 21, 1938, 
had not walked through the village since moving out in 1953. 

</P>
<P>
