<HEADLINE> Strawberry Goes 0-for-4 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Darryl Strawberry went 0-for-4 Tuesday night  
as he continued his comeback from a drug suspension at Triple-A 
Columbus. 
</P>
<P>
	Strawberry, hitting cleanup as the designated hitter, flied out  
to left field twice, grounded out and struck out looking in his 
four at-bats. Columbus beat Toledo 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
	``Each day is progress,'' Strawberry said after the game. ``If  
you haven't played as long as I have, the game is tough enough. 
</P>
<P>
	Strawberry is hitting .292 (7-for-24) with four RBIs and a  
stolen base with Columbus. 
</P>
<P>
	``My goal is to be in a situation where I feel good,'' he said.  
``And some days are better than other days.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
