<HEADLINE> United 4, MetroStars 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Jaime Moreno scored the go-ahead  
goal in the 42nd minute and D.C. United sent the New York-New 
Jersey MetroStars their sixth straight loss, 4-1 Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	United (15-7) has won three straight and leads Major League  
Soccer's East Division. 
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars (5-16), who have the league's worst record,  
scored on Sasa Curcic's penalty kick in the ninth minute, which 
ended their league-record scoreless streak at 375 minutes. They 
have not won a game in regulation since May 15. 
</P>
<P>
	United tied the score in the 21st minute when Carey Talley  
headed in Marco Etcheverry's free kick. 
</P>
<P>
	MetroStars defender Mike Petke was ejected in the 34th minute  
for his second yellow card -- he picked up the ball, kissed it and 
flipped it to referee Michael Kennedy. 
</P>
<P>
	Moreno beat goalkeeper Mike Ammann for a 2-1 lead eight minutes  
later. Ben Olson scored in the 71st and A.J. Wood connected off a 
cross from Talley four minutes later. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
