<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Colts Sign Walsh As Backup QB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- The Indianapolis Colts signed veteran  
quarterback Steve Walsh Wednesday and released quarterback Stoney 
Case. 
</P>
<P>
	The Colts are the sixth NFL team for Walsh, who was drafted by  
Dallas in the 1989 supplemental draft, traded to New Orleans in 
1990 and later played for Chicago, St. Louis and Tampa Bay. The 
6-foot-3, 215-pounder said he signed a two-year contract. 
</P>
<P>
	``He looked real good in the workout yesterday, better than I  
anticipated,'' coach Jim Mora said of Walsh, who had his first 
training camp practice Wednesday. ``I'm familiar with Steve. ... 
He's won, he's taken teams to the playoffs.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Case had played four seasons in Arizona and appeared of four  
games. 
</P>
<P>
	Walsh has played in only 65 games during his NFL career with 38  
starts. He completed 9-of-19 passes in five games for Tampa Bay 
last season. 
</P>
<P>
	``He took us to the playoffs in 1990,'' said Mora, who was his  
coach in New Orleans. ``He took Chicago to the playoffs in 1994. 
He's smart, he'll pick things up quickly. He won't require a lot of 
reps during the season. ... He'll be able to go in and still play 
and know what he is doing.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Case was signed to a $2 million contract that included a  
$500,000 signing bonus as an unrestricted free agent on March 8. 
</P>
<P>
	``We were not entirely pleased with the situation behind  
Peyton,'' said Mora, who saw the rookie take every snap last 
season. ``I believe this has upgraded us.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Case had been listed as the third quarterback on the team's  
depth chart. He completed 5-of-6 passes in Saturday's 9-6 loss at 
Chicago, accumulating 44 yards. He also had the team's longest run 
of the game, a 16-yard effort. 
</P>
<P>
	``Stoney did not progress like we hoped, and thought he would,''  
Mora said. ``It was close between him and Kelly Holcomb. ... Kelly 
had a little advantage because he'd been in our system before.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mora was uncertain if Walsh would play when the Colts host  
Cincinnati on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	``It would be very tough. It would be very limited from the  
standpoint of what plays we would call with him in there,'' Mora 
said. ``It's not an easy offense to learn.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
