<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Names New Toronto Bureau Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Tom Cohen, who has reported for The Associated  
Press from South Africa and Poland, has been named chief of bureau 
in Toronto. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Wednesday by AP President Louis D.  
Boccardi. 
</P>
<P>
	Cohen began his AP career in 1982 as a newsman in Jefferson City  
and moved to St. Louis in 1984. Two years later he transferred to 
the International Desk and in 1990 was assigned to Johannesburg as 
a correspondent. 
</P>
<P>
	Cohen, 42, was appointed news editor in Johannesburg four years  
later and was assigned to Warsaw as Central Europe correspondent in 
1998. 
</P>
<P>
	A native of St. Louis and a graduate of Tufts University, Cohen  
also worked as a reporter for the Columbia, Mo., Tribune. 
</P>
<P>
	He succeeds David Crary, who has been named a member of AP's  
national reporting team based in New York. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
