<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Texas Bootmaker Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NOCONA, Texas (AP) -- In a story Aug. 10 about the closing of two  
factories by Justin Industries, The Associated Press reported 
erroneously that the company sold 186.5 million pairs of boots in 
1997. The company reported $186.5 million in footwear sales that 
year. 



  	   	
</P>
