<HEADLINE> London Share Prices Rise / British Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Share prices rose Wednesday on the London Stock  
Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-Share index finished with  
a gain of 36.0 points, or 0.6 percent, at 6,014.4. 
</P>
<P>
	Volume was 922.3 million compared with 1.1 billion shares on  
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Support came from a less hawkish than expected Bank of England  
inflation report and traces of a rebound in beleaguered telecoms 
and banking stocks, even if some of the good mood was rubbed away 
late in the session by Wall Street's faltering performance. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
