<HEADLINE> AP Names New Salt Lake Bureau Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Jim Clarke, news editor for The Associated  
Press in Anchorage, Alaska, since 1998, has been promoted to news 
editor in Salt Lake City. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Wednesday by Salt Lake City Chief  
of Bureau William R. Beecham. 
</P>
<P>
	Clarke is a native of West Warwick, R.I., and a 1987 journalism  
graduate of George Washington University. He earned a master's 
degree in journalism from Columbia University in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
	Clarke, 33, worked for the Westerly (R.I.) Sun, the Fairfax  
(Va.) Journal and The Energy Daily in Washington, D.C., before 
joining the AP in Anchorage in 1993. He transferred to the 
Columbia, S.C., bureau in 1993 before returning to Anchorage in 
1995. 
  	   	
