<HEADLINE> Chiefs DE Browning May Miss Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RIVER FALLS, Wis. (AP) -- Defensive end John Browning had surgery  
on his right Achilles tendon Wednesday and likely is lost for the 
season, the Kansas City Chiefs said. 
</P>
<P>
	Coach Gunther Cunningham described the injury as being ``high up  
in the Achilles,'' calling that a positive. But he said it was 
unknown how long Browning would be out. 
</P>
<P>
	Cunningham said Brown's leg ``rolled'' during a drill Monday  
morning. 
</P>
<P>
	Browning, a third-round pick of the Chiefs in 1996, started the  
first eight games last season before a back injury sidelined him 
for the year. His quickness makes him a strong pass rusher from 
