<HEADLINE> Marlins' Fernandez May Miss a Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Florida Marlins pitcher Alex Fernandez may receive  
a cortisone shot Thursday in his sore right shoulder, which would 
force him to miss a start. 
</P>
<P>
	Fernandez, who pitched six innings in Wednesday's 6-5 victory  
over San Francisco, will visit Dr. James Andrews in Birmingham, 
Ala. during the team's off-day Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
