<HEADLINE> European Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- European shares closed higher Wednesday as  
concerns eased over a possible interest rate rise. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 592 European companies rose 1.93  
points Wednesday, or 0.7 percent, to close at 293.91. The best 
performing index was basic resources, up 2.1 percent, followed by 
technology, up 1.8 percent, and banks, up 1.7 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 297 companies in  
countries that joined the single currency, closed up 1.75 points at 
305.83. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro came under pressure, falling to a low of $1.0674, after  
Germany reported flat industrial output in June from May, 
disappointing expectations of a 1.0 percent rise. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index rose 16.29 points to 3,551.39,  
while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index closed up 17.93 points at 3,509.32. 
</P>
<P>
	In domestic markets, Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index rose 0.4  
percent to 5,019.69. 
</P>
<P>
	The Paris CAC-40 index rose 0.6 percent to 4,268.95, Amsterdam's  
AEX Index rose 0.9 percent, Milan's MIBtel index rose 0.4 percent 
to 31,889 and London's FTSE 100 index of blue-chip shares rose 0.6 
percent to 6,014.40. 
</P>
<P>
	A benign inflation report from France eased concern that  
interest rates in Europe may rise. 
  	   	
</P>
